Passed more than 6 years since I have converted the arcade game City Connection
to ZX Spectrum. I never had any luck when tried to comercialize this game.

So, now I'm giving it away, in form of snapshot that can be run in Amiga's
ZX Spectrum emulator.

This is the 48K version, but there is also a much better version to be run
in 128K Spectrums. Whenever somebody manages to code a emulator for those
series of Spectrums, I'll give away the 128K version too. The 128K version
is even better than the original arcade.

It is recommended something like a Amiga 1200 with Fast RAM or a better
Amiga, or else the game won't be playable at all.

Although there is an option that let's you play with an Amiga joystick
through Kempston emulation, it is recommend that you use the keyboard instead,
because the game needs two buttons, one to fire oil can and the other to jump.
Since Spectrum joysticks usually hadn't two buttons, to fire oil cans you have
to press both fire button as well one of left, right or down directions. If
you press fire button alone it car will jump. If you press both up and fire
it will jump higher. Have fun!

